com.hazelcast.spi

Class LiveOperations

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.spi.LiveOperations

  • public final class LiveOperations
extends Object
    Collections per member the callIds of all live operations. The Trace is not thread-safe and is recycled. This data-structure can be optimized to generate less litter. Instead of using an ArrayList for Long objects, use an array for primitive longs. Also the lists don't need to be recreated every time the LiveOperationsTracker.populate(LiveOperations) method is called; they could be recycled. This would be easy to do since the LiveOperations is not used by a single thread.
